28#include <sys/zio.h>
29#include <sys/spa.h>
30#include <sys/zfs_acl.h>
31#include <sys/zfs_ioctl.h>
32#include <sys/fs/zfs.h>
33
34#include "zfs_prop.h"
35
36#if defined(_KERNEL)
37#include <sys/systm.h>
38#else
39#include <stdlib.h>
40#include <string.h>

43
44static zprop_desc_t zpool_prop_table[ZPOOL_NUM_PROPS];
45
46zprop_desc_t *
47zpool_prop_get_table(void)
48{
49 return (zpool_prop_table);
50}
51
52void
53zpool_prop_init(void)
54{
55 static zprop_index_t boolean_table[] = {
56 { "off", 0},
57 { "on", 1},
58 { NULL }
59 };
60
61 static zprop_index_t failuremode_table[] = {
62 { "wait", ZIO_FAILURE_MODE_WAIT },
63 { "continue", ZIO_FAILURE_MODE_CONTINUE },
64 { "panic", ZIO_FAILURE_MODE_PANIC },
65 { NULL }
66 };
67
68 /* string properties */
69 zprop_register_string(ZPOOL_PROP_ALTROOT, "altroot", NULL, PROP_DEFAULT,
70 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<path>", "ALTROOT");
71 zprop_register_string(ZPOOL_PROP_BOOTFS, "bootfs", NULL, PROP_DEFAULT,
72 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<filesystem>", "BOOTFS");
73 zprop_register_string(ZPOOL_PROP_CACHEFILE, "cachefile", NULL,
74 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<file> | none", "CACHEFILE");
75 zprop_register_string(ZPOOL_PROP_COMMENT, "comment", NULL,
76 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<comment-string>", "COMMENT");
77
78 /* readonly number properties */
79 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_SIZE, "size", 0, PROP_READONLY,
80 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<size>", "SIZE");
81 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_FREE, "free", 0, PROP_READONLY,
82 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<size>", "FREE");
83 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_FREEING, "freeing", 0, PROP_READONLY,
84 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<size>", "FREEING");
85 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_LEAKED, "leaked", 0, PROP_READONLY,
86 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<size>", "LEAKED");
87 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_ALLOCATED, "allocated", 0,
88 PROP_READONLY, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<size>", "ALLOC");
89 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_EXPANDSZ, "expandsize", 0,
90 PROP_READONLY, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<size>", "EXPANDSZ");
91 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_FRAGMENTATION, "fragmentation", 0,
92 PROP_READONLY, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<percent>", "FRAG");
93 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_CAPACITY, "capacity", 0, PROP_READONLY,
94 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<size>", "CAP");
95 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_GUID, "guid", 0, PROP_READONLY,
96 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<guid>", "GUID");
97 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_HEALTH, "health", 0, PROP_READONLY,
98 ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<state>", "HEALTH");
99 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_DEDUPRATIO, "dedupratio", 0,
100 PROP_READONLY, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<1.00x or higher if deduped>",
101 "DEDUP");
102
103 /* default number properties */
104 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_VERSION, "version", SPA_VERSION,
105 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<version>", "VERSION");
106 zprop_register_number(ZPOOL_PROP_DEDUPDITTO, "dedupditto", 0,
107 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "<threshold (min 100)>", "DEDUPDITTO");
108
109 /* default index (boolean) properties */
110 zprop_register_index(ZPOOL_PROP_DELEGATION, "delegation", 1,
111 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "on | off", "DELEGATION",
112 boolean_table);
113 zprop_register_index(ZPOOL_PROP_AUTOREPLACE, "autoreplace", 0,
114 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "on | off", "REPLACE", boolean_table);
115 zprop_register_index(ZPOOL_PROP_LISTSNAPS, "listsnapshots", 0,
116 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "on | off", "LISTSNAPS",
117 boolean_table);
118 zprop_register_index(ZPOOL_PROP_AUTOEXPAND, "autoexpand", 0,
119 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "on | off", "EXPAND", boolean_table);
120 zprop_register_index(ZPOOL_PROP_READONLY, "readonly", 0,
121 PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "on | off", "RDONLY", boolean_table);
122
123 /* default index properties */
124 zprop_register_index(ZPOOL_PROP_FAILUREMODE, "failmode",
125 ZIO_FAILURE_MODE_WAIT, PROP_DEFAULT, ZFS_TYPE_POOL,
126 "wait | continue | panic", "FAILMODE", failuremode_table);
127
128 /* hidden properties */
129 zprop_register_hidden(ZPOOL_PROP_NAME, "name", PROP_TYPE_STRING,
130 PROP_READONLY, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "NAME");
131 zprop_register_hidden(ZPOOL_PROP_MAXBLOCKSIZE, "maxblocksize",
132 PROP_TYPE_NUMBER, PROP_READONLY, ZFS_TYPE_POOL, "MAXBLOCKSIZE");
133}
134
135/*
136 * Given a property name and its type, returns the corresponding property ID.
137 */
138zpool_prop_t
139zpool_name_to_prop(const char *propname)
140{
141 return (zprop_name_to_prop(propname, ZFS_TYPE_POOL));
142}
143
144/*
145 * Given a pool property ID, returns the corresponding name.
146 * Assuming the pool propety ID is valid.
147 */
148const char *
149zpool_prop_to_name(zpool_prop_t prop)
150{
151 return (zpool_prop_table[prop].pd_name);
152}
153
154zprop_type_t
155zpool_prop_get_type(zpool_prop_t prop)
156{
157 return (zpool_prop_table[prop].pd_proptype);
158}
159
160boolean_t
161zpool_prop_readonly(zpool_prop_t prop)
162{
163 return (zpool_prop_table[prop].pd_attr == PROP_READONLY);
164}
165
166const char *
167zpool_prop_default_string(zpool_prop_t prop)
168{
169 return (zpool_prop_table[prop].pd_strdefault);
170}
171
172uint64_t
173zpool_prop_default_numeric(zpool_prop_t prop)
174{
175 return (zpool_prop_table[prop].pd_numdefault);
176}
177
178/*
179 * Returns true if this is a valid feature@ property.
180 */
181boolean_t
182zpool_prop_feature(const char *name)
183{
184 static const char *prefix = "feature@";
185 return (strncmp(name, prefix, strlen(prefix)) == 0);
186}
187
188/*
189 * Returns true if this is a valid unsupported@ property.
190 */
191boolean_t
192zpool_prop_unsupported(const char *name)
193{
194 static const char *prefix = "unsupported@";
195 return (strncmp(name, prefix, strlen(prefix)) == 0);
196}
197
198int
199zpool_prop_string_to_index(zpool_prop_t prop, const char *string,
200 uint64_t *index)
201{
202 return (zprop_string_to_index(prop, string, index, ZFS_TYPE_POOL));
203}
204
205int
206zpool_prop_index_to_string(zpool_prop_t prop, uint64_t index,
207 const char **string)
208{
209 return (zprop_index_to_string(prop, index, string, ZFS_TYPE_POOL));
210}
211
212uint64_t
213zpool_prop_random_value(zpool_prop_t prop, uint64_t seed)
214{
215 return (zprop_random_value(prop, seed, ZFS_TYPE_POOL));
216}

227zpool_prop_column_name(zpool_prop_t prop)

230}
231
232boolean_t
233zpool_prop_align_right(zpool_prop_t prop)
234{
235 return (zpool_prop_table[prop].pd_rightalign);
236}
